# Backend — unit tests required

When you **add or change backend logic** (services, controllers, config, repositories, DTOs, security, etc.), treat the task as incomplete until **tests are green**.

## What to do

1. After substantive edits under `Backend/`, run unit tests from the backend module:

   ```bash
   cd Backend && mvn test
   ```

2. If any test **fails**, **fix the code or update the tests** so `mvn test` passes. Do not leave the backend in a broken-test state when the change was intentional (refactors, renames, new behavior).

3. If you **add new behavior**, extend or add tests in `Backend/src/test/java/` when it is reasonable for the change (same package patterns as existing tests).

## Exceptions

- Trivial edits (comments only, formatting only) may skip a full run if CI/local verification is obviously unnecessary—but when in doubt, run `mvn test`.

## Project note

Surefire may use `-Dnet.bytebuddy.experimental=true` (see `Backend/pom.xml`) for newer JDKs; use the normal Maven command above so the same configuration applies.
